```

In this updated version, we use the `time.Time` struct and its `time.Date` function to calculate the duration until the next desired execution time (12 AM). We add 1 day to the current date and set the time to 0 hours, 0 minutes, and 0 seconds.

Then, we use `time.Sleep` to wait until the next execution time. The program will pause until 12 AM of the next day.

After that, you can insert your cron job logic where the comment `Add your cron job logic here...` is placed. The code inside that section will run at 12 AM each day. You can customize this section with your specific cron job implementation.

Note that after running the cron job once, the application can exit or continue with other application logic as desired.

