In this example, we have an empty `[]string` slice associated with the `key1` key.

However, you can still use `append()` to append values to the slice associated with `key1`. The `append(data["key1"], "value1", "value2")` expression creates a new slice containing the appended values. The updated slice is then assigned to `data["key1"]`.

After appending, the output will display the key-value pairs of the map.

If the `[]string` slice is empty initially, using `append()` directly will properly populate the slice with the desired values.

